You are building a React Native mobile app using Expo (with Expo Router for file-based routing) targeting iOS and Android, with a companion website.

## Stack
- Framework: Expo SDK (latest), Expo Router v3
- Styling: NativeWind (Tailwind for React Native)
- Backend: Supabase (auth, database, realtime, storage)
- Hosting (web): Cloudflare Pages
- Language: TypeScript throughout

## Supabase
- Client is initialized in lib/supabase.ts using EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- Use Supabase Auth for all authentication (email/password to start)
- Always use Row Level Security (RLS) on every table
- Prefer Supabase realtime subscriptions over polling where live data is needed

## Cloudflare (not Vercel)
- Do NOT suggest or generate any Vercel config, next.config.js, or vercel.json
- Web deployment targets Cloudflare Pages
- Use wrangler.toml for any Cloudflare config
- Edge-compatible code only for any web server logic

## Code style
- Functional components only, no class components
- Always use TypeScript — no `any` types
- File-based routing via Expo Router — screens live in app/
- Shared components live in components/
- Supabase queries live in lib/ or hooks/
- Use custom hooks (useAuth, useShifts etc.) to wrap Supabase calls

## Do not
- Do not use React Navigation directly (Expo Router handles routing)
- Do not use Vercel, Next.js API routes, or any Node.js server
- Do not use local state for data that belongs in Supabase
- Do not hardcode any API keys
